ntence\": \"\\\"Heat training is the new altitude training,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 4610, \"to\": 4664, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Heat training\", \"from\": 4611, \"to\": 4624}, {\"ngram\": \"the new altitude training\", \"from\": 4628, \"to\": 4653}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Chris Minson, a physiologist at the University of Oregon,foundthat training to withstand heat benefits athletes even in cool-weather races.\", \"from\": 4665, \"to\": 4804, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Chris Minson\", \"from\": 4665, \"to\": 4677}, {\"ngram\": \"a physiologist\", \"from\": 4679, \"to\": 4693}, {\"ngram\": \"the University\", \"from\": 4697, \"to\": 4711}, {\"ngram\": \"Oregon\", \"from\": 4715, \"to\": 4721}, {\"ngram\": \"heat benefits athletes\", \"from\": 4754, \"to\": 4776}, {\"ngram\": \"cool-weather races\", \"from\": 4785, \"to\": 4803}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He saw that if cyclists trained in 104-degree heat for 10 days, their VO2 max-the maximum amount of oxygen one's body can take in and use while exercising-got a 5 percent boost.\", \"from\": 4805, \"to\": 4982, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"cyclists\", \"from\": 4820, \"to\": 4828}, {\"ngram\": \"104-degree heat\", \"from\": 4840, \"to\": 4855}, {\"ngram\": \"10 days\", \"from\": 4860, \"to\": 4867}, {\"ngram\": \"their VO2 max\", \"from\": 4869, \"to\": 4882}, {\"ngram\": \"the maximum amount\", \"from\": 4883, \"to\": 4901}, {\"ngram\": \"oxygen one's body\", \"from\": 4905, \"to\": 4922}, {\"ngram\": \"a 5 percent boost\", \"from\": 4964, \"to\": 4981}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their one-hour time trial got6 percent faster, even in temperate conditions.\", \"from\": 4983, \"to\": 5059, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their one-hour time trial got6 percent\", \"from\": 4983, \"to\": 5021}, {\"ngram\": \"temperate conditions\", \"from\": 5038, \"to\": 5058}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Olympians in Parishave reportedspending time in saunas and training in extra layers of clothing to prepare.\", \"from\": 5060, \"to\": 5167, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Olympians\", \"from\": 5060, \"to\": 5069}, {\"ngram\": \"Parishave\", \"from\": 5073, \"to\": 5082}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 5100, \"to\": 5104}, {\"ngram\": \"saunas\", \"from\": 5108, \"to\": 5114}, {\"ngram\": \"training\", \"from\": 5119, \"to\": 5127}, {\"ngram\": \"extra layers\", \"from\": 5131, \"to\": 5143}, {\"ngram\": \"clothing\", \"from\": 5147, \"to\": 5155}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I guarantee everybody in Paris who's doing anything in the track-and-field events that are longer than the 400 meter probably have gone through some sort of heat-acclimation protocol,\\\" Wilkins told me.\", \"from\": 5168, \"to\": 5370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5194, \"end\": 5199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999799911, \"rank\": 2.019054073567133e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 5354, \"end\": 5361, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hubert_Wilkins\", \"score\": 0.9961283565835993, \"rank\": 0.003859366747309105, \"text\": \"Wilkins\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hubert_Wilkins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hubert_Wilkins\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everybody\", \"from\": 5181, \"to\": 5190}, {\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 5212, \"to\": 5220}, {\"ngram\": \"the track-and-field events\", \"from\": 5224, \"to\": 5250}, {\"ngram\": \"the 400 meter\", \"from\": 5272, \"to\": 5285}, {\"ngram\": \"some sort\", \"from\": 5313, \"to\": 5322}, {\"ngram\": \"heat-acclimation protocol\", \"from\": 5326, \"to\": 5351}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wilkins was part of a team sponsored by Nike that in 2016 attempted to create the perfect conditions in which to run the world's fastest marathon.\", \"from\": 5374, \"to\": 5520, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5414, \"end\": 5418, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"score\": 0.9999999134133797, \"rank\": 8.658626139138284e-08, \"text\": \"Nike\", \"types\": [\"Q728\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/MIM-3_Nike_Ajax\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wilkins\", \"from\": 5374, \"to\": 5381}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 5386, \"to\": 5390}, {\"ngram\": \"a team\", \"from\": 5394, \"to\": 5400}, {\"ngram\": \"the perfect conditions\", \"from\": 5452, \"to\": 5474}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's fastest marathon\", \"from\": 5491, \"to\": 5519}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Engineers and physiologists designed every element of the event; the Kenyan marathoner Eliud Kipchoge ran a private race at an ideal temperature in advanced clothing and with other runners in front of him to cut wind resistance.\", \"from\": 5521, \"to\": 5749, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5608, \"end\": 5622, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eliud Kipchoge\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eliud_Kipchoge\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Engineers\", \"from\": 5521, \"to\": 5530}, {\"ngram\": \"physiologists\", \"from\": 5535, \"to\": 5548}, {\"ngram\": \"every element\", \"from\": 5558, \"to\": 5571}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 5575, \"to\": 5584}, {\"ngram\": \"a private race\", \"from\": 5627, \"to\": 5641}, {\"ngram\": \"an ideal temperature\", \"from\": 5645, \"to\": 5665}, {\"ngram\": \"advanced clothing\", \"from\": 5669, \"to\": 5686}, {\"ngram\": \"other runners\", \"from\": 5696, \"to\": 5709}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 5713, \"to\": 5718}, {\"ngram\": \"wind resistance\", \"from\": 5733, \"to\": 5748}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He ran it in two hours and 25 seconds.\", \"from\": 5750, \"to\": 5788, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"two hours\", \"from\": 5763, \"to\": 5772}, {\"ngram\": \"25 seconds\", \"from\": 5777, \"to\": 5787}]}, {\"sentence\": \"High-tech shoes made thebiggest difference, reducing his energy costs by 4 percent.\", \"from\": 5789, \"to\": 5872, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"High-tech shoes\", \"from\": 5789, \"to\": 5804}, {\"ngram\": \"thebiggest difference\", \"from\": 5810, \"to\": 5831}, {\"ngram\": \"his energy costs\", \"from\": 5842, \"to\": 5858}, {\"ngram\": \"4 percent\", \"from\": 5862, \"to\": 5871}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a similar experiment a few years later, Kipchoge broke the two-hour barrier, but the entire enterprise was so heavily engineered that itdidn't count as a true \\\"marathon\\\"for world-record-setting purposes.\", \"from\": 5873, \"to\": 6079, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a similar experiment\", \"from\": 5876, \"to\": 5896}, {\"ngram\": \"Kipchoge\", \"from\": 5916, \"to\": 5924}, {\"ngram\": \"the two-hour barrier\", \"from\": 5931, \"to\": 5951}, {\"ngram\": \"the entire enterprise\", \"from\": 5957, \"to\": 5978}, {\"ngram\": \"itdidn't\", \"from\": 6010, \"to\": 6018}, {\"ngram\": \"a true \\\"marathon\\\"for world-record-setting purposes\", \"from\": 6028, \"to\": 6078}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The lesson?\", \"from\": 6083, \"to\": 6094, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The lesson\", \"from\": 6083, \"to\": 6093}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Advances in technology-training routines, nutrition, clothing, and more-are what support incredibly talented athletes like Kipchoge in reaching new heights of human performance.\", \"from\": 6095, \"to\": 6272, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Advances\", \"from\": 6095, \"to\": 6103}, {\"ngram\": \"technology-training routines\", \"from\": 6107, \"to\": 6135}, {\"ngram\": \"nutrition\", \"from\": 6137, \"to\": 6146}, {\"ngram\": \"clothing\", \"from\": 6148, \"to\": 6156}, {\"ngram\": \"incredibly talented athletes\", \"from\": 6184, \"to\": 6212}, {\"ngram\": \"Kipchoge\", \"from\": 6218, \"to\": 6226}, {\"ngram\": \"new heights\", \"from\": 6239, \"to\": 6250}, {\"ngram\": \"human performance\", \"from\": 6254, \"to\": 6271}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Today's elite runners and cyclists are no different from the ones who competed in the 1950s and '60s: Humans have certainly not evolved into a faster species in that time.\", \"from\": 6276, \"to\": 6447, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Today's elite runners\", \"from\": 6276, \"to\": 6297}, {\"ngram\": \"cyclists\", \"from\": 6302, \"to\": 6310}, {\"ngram\": \"the ones\", \"from\": 6333, \"to\": 6341}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1950s\", \"from\": 6358, \"to\": 6367}, {\"ngram\": \"60s\", \"from\": 6373, \"to\": 6376}, {\"ngram\": \"Humans\", \"from\": 6378, \"to\": 6384}, {\"ngram\": \"a faster species\", \"from\": 6417, \"to\": 6433}, {\"ngram\": \"that time\", \"from\": 6437, \"to\": 6446}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men winning the Tour de France today, Joyner said, \\\"are probably not any physiologically better than the great Eddy Merckx,\\\" who won the event five times in the '60s and '70s.\", \"from\": 6448, \"to\": 6627, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6468, \"end\": 6482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 3.592668193039394e-12, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 6563, \"end\": 6574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1732717108467063e-29, \"text\": \"Eddy Merckx\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eddy_Merckx\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The men\", \"from\": 6448, \"to\": 6455}, {\"ngram\": \"Joyner\", \"from\": 6490, \"to\": 6496}, {\"ngram\": \"the event\", \"from\": 6585, \"to\": 6594}, {\"ngram\": \"60s\", \"from\": 6614, \"to\": 6617}, {\"ngram\": \"70s\", \"from\": 6623, \"to\": 6626}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But most other elements of elite sport have changed.\", \"from\": 6628, \"to\": 6680, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"most other elements\", \"from\": 6632, \"to\": 6651}, {\"ngram\": \"elite sport\", \"from\": 6655, \"to\": 6666}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bikes now allow riders to go faster with less energy input.\", \"from\": 6681, \"to\": 6740, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bikes\", \"from\": 6681, \"to\": 6686}, {\"ngram\": \"riders\", \"from\": 6697, \"to\": 6703}, {\"ngram\": \"less energy input\", \"from\": 6722, \"to\": 6739}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The tracks that runners use have improved, reducing energy waste.\", \"from\": 6741, \"to\": 6806, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The tracks\", \"from\": 6741, \"to\": 6751}, {\"ngram\": \"runners\", \"from\": 6757, \"to\": 6764}, {\"ngram\": \"energy waste\", \"from\": 6793, \"to\": 6805}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shoe technology has advanced dramatically.\", \"from\": 6807, \"to\": 6849, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Shoe technology\", \"from\": 6807, \"to\": 6822}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not see any slowing of world records, as long as the technology continues to be good and as long as people continue to focus on really setting up these races to get optimal performances,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 6850, \"to\": 7052, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any slowing\", \"from\": 6864, \"to\": 6875}, {\"ngram\": \"world records\", \"from\": 6879, \"to\": 6892}, {\"ngram\": \"the technology\", \"from\": 6905, \"to\": 6919}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 6956, \"to\": 6962}, {\"ngram\": \"these races\", \"from\": 7002, \"to\": 7013}, {\"ngram\": \"optimal performances\", \"from\": 7021, \"to\": 7041}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a1991 paper, Joyner calculated the likely best possible VO2 max,lactate threshold, and running economy a person can achieve.\", \"from\": 7056, \"to\": 7183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7115, \"end\": 7122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/VO2_max\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"VO2 max\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/VO2_max\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/VO2_max\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a1991 paper\", \"from\": 7059, \"to\": 7070}, {\"ngram\": \"Joyner\", \"from\": 7072, \"to\": 7078}, {\"ngram\": \"lactate threshold\", \"from\": 7123, \"to\": 7140}, {\"ngram\": \"running economy\", \"from\": 7146, \"to\": 7161}, {\"ngram\": \"a person\", \"from\": 7162, \"to\": 7170}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If a runner could achieve all three at the same time, he wrote in the paper, the fastest possible marathon in natural conditions would be run in one hour, 57 minutes, and 58 seconds.\", \"from\": 7184, \"to\": 7366, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a runner\", \"from\": 7187, \"to\": 7195}, {\"ngram\": \"the same time\", \"from\": 7223, \"to\": 7236}, {\"ngram\": \"the paper\", \"from\": 7250, \"to\": 7259}, {\"ngram\": \"the fastest possible marathon\", \"from\": 7261, \"to\": 7290}, {\"ngram\": \"natural conditions\", \"from\": 7294, \"to\": 7312}, {\"ngram\": \"one hour\", \"from\": 7329, \"to\": 7337}, {\"ngram\": \"57 minutes\", \"from\": 7339, \"to\": 7349}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That record has still not been achieved, but he imagines it will be, regardless of the march of climate change.\", \"from\": 7367, \"to\": 7478, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"That record\", \"from\": 7367, \"to\": 7378}, {\"ngram\": \"the march\", \"from\": 7450, \"to\": 7459}, {\"ngram\": \"climate change\", \"from\": 7463, \"to\": 7477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wilkins is slightly less optimistic.\", \"from\": 7482, \"to\": 7518, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wilkins\", \"from\": 7482, \"to\": 7489}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I grew up in the West.\", \"from\": 7519, \"to\": 7542, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 7533, \"to\": 7541}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So I have watched fire seasons and how long they have gotten since I was a kid,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 7543, \"to\": 7632, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"fire seasons\", \"from\": 7561, \"to\": 7573}, {\"ngram\": \"a kid\", \"from\": 7616, \"to\": 7621}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He has a visceral sense of how climate change might be progressing faster than many people understand.\", \"from\": 7633, \"to\": 7735, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a visceral sense\", \"from\": 7640, \"to\": 7656}, {\"ngram\": \"climate change\", \"from\": 7664, \"to\": 7678}, {\"ngram\": \"many people\", \"from\": 7712, \"to\": 7723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So he can imagine that, 20 years from now, the fastest marathon time might slip back to 2 hours 10 minutes-that, especially for long-duration events that are impractical to hold indoors, times may begin to slow as temperatures keep rising.\", \"from\": 7736, \"to\": 7975, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the fastest marathon time\", \"from\": 7779, \"to\": 7804}, {\"ngram\": \"2 hours\", \"from\": 7824, \"to\": 7831}, {\"ngram\": \"long-duration events\", \"from\": 7864, \"to\": 7884}, {\"ngram\": \"indoors\", \"from\": 7914, \"to\": 7921}, {\"ngram\": \"times\", \"from\": 7923, \"to\": 7928}, {\"ngram\": \"temperatures\", \"from\": 7950, \"to\": 7962}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That might discourage more people from entering the sport, which would have a ripple effect of degrading the quality of competitions overall.\", \"from\": 7976, \"to\": 8117, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"more people\", \"from\": 7998, \"to\": 8009}, {\"ngram\": \"the sport\", \"from\": 8024, \"to\": 8033}, {\"ngram\": \"a ripple effect\", \"from\": 8052, \"to\": 8067}, {\"ngram\": \"the quality\", \"from\": 8081, \"to\": 8092}, {\"ngram\": \"competitions\", \"from\": 8096, \"to\": 8108}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The less people you have in any sport, the lower the probability you have of finding the right factors of physiology and psychology in a human being that can actually perform these amazing feats,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 8118, \"to\": 8324, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any sport\", \"from\": 8147, \"to\": 8156}, {\"ngram\": \"the lower the probability\", \"from\": 8158, \"to\": 8183}, {\"ngram\": \"the right factors\", \"from\": 8204, \"to\": 8221}, {\"ngram\": \"physiology\", \"from\": 8225, \"to\": 8235}, {\"ngram\": \"psychology\", \"from\": 8240, \"to\": 8250}, {\"ngram\": \"a human being\", \"from\": 8254, \"to\": 8267}, {\"ngram\": \"these amazing feats\", \"from\": 8294, \"to\": 8313}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Still, each time our conversation turned to the possibility that human potential in sport might truly be limited by the warming of the planet, Wilkins would pause and backtrack.\", \"from\": 8328, \"to\": 8505, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8471, \"end\": 8478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hubert_Wilkins\", \"score\": 0.9961283565835993, \"rank\": 0.003859366747309105, \"text\": \"Wilkins\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hubert_Wilkins\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hubert_Wilkins\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our conversation\", \"from\": 8345, \"to\": 8361}, {\"ngram\": \"the possibility\", \"from\": 8372, \"to\": 8387}, {\"ngram\": \"human potential\", \"from\": 8393, \"to\": 8408}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 8412, \"to\": 8417}, {\"ngram\": \"the warming\", \"from\": 8444, \"to\": 8455}, {\"ngram\": \"the planet\", \"from\": 8459, \"to\": 8469}, {\"ngram\": \"backtrack\", \"from\": 8495, \"to\": 8504}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Whenever I start to put hard limits on humans, I also start to hesitate,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 8509, \"to\": 8592, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"hard limits\", \"from\": 8534, \"to\": 8545}, {\"ngram\": \"humans\", \"from\": 8549, \"to\": 8555}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Limits on humans in sports have never proved true in the past.\", \"from\": 8593, \"to\": 8655, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Limits\", \"from\": 8593, \"to\": 8599}, {\"ngram\": \"humans\", \"from\": 8603, \"to\": 8609}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 8613, \"to\": 8619}, {\"ngram\": \"the past\", \"from\": 8646, \"to\": 8654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And technology we can not imagine today may emerge to help eschew the problem heat poses.\", \"from\": 8656, \"to\": 8745, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"technology\", \"from\": 8660, \"to\": 8670}, {\"ngram\": \"the problem\", \"from\": 8722, \"to\": 8733}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are a creative species,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 8746, \"to\": 8783, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a creative species\", \"from\": 8754, \"to\": 8772}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Our bodies might not be able to adapt so quickly to the heat, but our behavior, and the ways we decide to handle this challenge, certainly could.\", \"from\": 8784, \"to\": 8929, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Our bodies\", \"from\": 8784, \"to\": 8794}, {\"ngram\": \"the heat\", \"from\": 8836, \"to\": 8844}, {\"ngram\": \"this challenge\", \"from\": 8897, \"to\": 8911}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TheAtlantic.com \\u00a92026The Atlantic Monthly Group.\", \"from\": 8931, \"to\": 8979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8956, \"end\": 8972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Atlantic Monthly\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic